#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Einführung"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:23
msgid ""
"When Extinction Rebellion first hit the world’s headlines, it was because "
"rebels were willing to break the law to raise awareness about the climate "
"crisis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:25
msgid ""
"But last year saw a marked shift in climate activism’s relationship with the "
"law. Across the globe communities and organisations have started to use "
"existing laws, and even create new ones, to hold governments and polluting "
"corporations to account."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:27
msgid ""
"We’ve seen young people all around the world, from Mexico to South Korea, "
"sue their governments for negligent climate policy. We’ve seen Portuguese "
"youth activists have their landmark case against all 33 European states fast-"
"tracked to the European Court of Human Rights. And we’ve seen a vast array "
"of lawsuits brought against major oil firms by US states, cities, and "
"communities."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:29
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image17-47.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "*The Portuguese youth activists taking their case to the European Court of Human Rights. Photos: GLAN*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:33
msgid ""
"You can find out more about this flurry of climate litigation in ***Must "
"Reads***, along with some examples where the law is not so much an *asset* "
"to the climate cause as an *ass*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:35
msgid ""
"The focus meanwhile for this legal-eagle special issue will be on two "
"campaigns aiming to create new laws for activists to harness in the future."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:37
msgid ""
"The [Climate & Ecological Emergency Bill](https://www.ceebill.uk/) was "
"introduced to UK’s Parliament in September and aims to turn XR’s demands "
"into British law. As well as building local support, the team behind it have "
"expanded the legislation so it can be applied to any government in the run "
"up to COP26."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:39
msgid ""
"Meanwhile thanks to the [Stop Ecocide](https://www.stopecocide.earth/) "
"campaign, a team of international lawyers are drafting new legislation to "
"make Ecocide a crime. One day soon, negligent politicians and polluting CEOs "
"could find themselves in the dock of the International Criminal Court!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:41
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image9-47.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Politicians lose their spines before a media mogul in Melbourne. So that’s what happens.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:45
msgid ""
"To find out more about both campaigns and get involved, head over to Action "
"Highlights. Aside from legal matters, we’ve also got special reports on "
"rebellion waves in Israel and Australia, and uncover a terrible ecological "
"crime happening in Southern Africa."
msgstr ""

