#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "CEE Bill Going Global for COP26"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Ongoing | UK & International**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:72
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image25-47.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Rebels rally outside as the CEE Bill is introduced to politicians in the British Parliament.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:76
msgid ""
"A campaign to introduce major new climate-ecology legislation in the UK now "
"has the backing of [89 Ministers of Parliament](https://www.ceebill.uk/"
"allies_and_supporters?e%3D5b49b7d6f1979d3b284d4310514a67b4%26utm_source"
"%3Dceebill%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3D2020_12_23_good_tidi%26n"
"%3D2/) (MPs) who together represent 6 million citizens, as well as 5 "
"councils and Greenpeace UK."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:78
msgid ""
"Written by an alliance of scientists, lawyers, economists and activists "
"(including rebels), the [Climate and Ecological Emergency (CEE) Bill]"
"(https://www.ceebill.uk/) will [legally require](https://www.ceebill.uk/"
"bill/) the UK Government to take urgent and far-reaching climate action, "
"with the terms directed by a Citizens’ Assembly as well as MPs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:80
msgid ""
"The CEE Bill would also force the UK to take responsibility for its overseas "
"carbon and ecological footprint (currently ignored), and do its fair share "
"in reducing global emissions considering it is an [advanced economy](https://"
"www.investopedia.com/terms/a/advanced-economies.asp/)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:82
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image1-47.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "*The UK’s only Green Party MP accepts a letter from young rebels before tabling the CEE Bill.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:86
msgid ""
"With [COP26](https://ukcop26.org/) scheduled for this November, the team "
"behind the CEE Bill have broadened its contents to create a universal "
"blueprint of emergency measures. The [Face the Future 10-Point Plan](https://"
"docs.google.com/document/d/1Rl7V_Gv_eaCvMbesir3FKsgjFWjHbMed5TEG1wbeobA/"
"edit/) could apply to the government of any advanced economy, and even be "
"integrated into the Paris Agreement."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:88
msgid ""
"The Face The Future team are now calling on activists and organisations "
"around the world to pressure their government to sign up to these 10 "
"principles. The Plan has already been backed by rebels in the UK, France, "
"Italy and Germany."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:90
msgid ""
"If you would like your government to Face The Future in time for COP26, then "
"check out these [campaigning ideas](https://docs.google.com/document/"
"d/1rdhOFvAtz2zfFqPpiKMxMtWmXfxFN-IK5oO8MzEWRz0/edit/), take this [online "
"training on engaging political representatives](https://www.youtube.com/"
"watch?v%3DGIVblhYewwM%26feature%3Dyoutu.be/), and use these [templates]"
"(https://www.ceebill.uk/writetoyourmp?utm_campaign%3D2020_12_23_good_tidi"
"%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_source%3Dceebill/) to start lobbying your local "
"politicians."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:92
msgid ""
"You could even represent your country in upcoming Face The Future meetings - "
"contact [nessyhainesmatos@ceebill.uk](mailto:nessyhainesmatos@ceebill.uk) "
"for more information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "Making Ecocide History!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Ongoing | International**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:98
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image5-47.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:100
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Polly Higgins. Photo: Wikipedia*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:102
msgid ""
"Fifteen years ago, while looking out of a window during a court case, "
"barrister Polly Higgins [had a thought](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v"
"%3D8EuxYzQ65H4/): “The earth is in need of a good lawyer”. So began her "
"lifelong battle to make ecocide - widespread, severe, or systematic "
"destruction of nature - a crime prosecutable in court."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:104
msgid ""
"Although Polly Higgins sadly died in 2019, this idea - shared by many others "
"worldwide - is [sparking a revolution](https://www.independent.co.uk/"
"environment/climate-change/ecocide-war-crimes-pollution-b1774578.html/)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:106
msgid ""
"In December 2019, island states Vanuatu and the Maldives called for “serious "
"consideration” of the criminalisation of ecocide at an annual assembly of "
"the International Criminal Court (ICC). In December, Belgium became the "
"first European nation to raise the issue at the ICC. And right now "
"international lawyers are [working on a legal definition of ecocide](https://"
"www.stopecocide.earth/expert-drafting-panel/) as an international crime that "
"could sit alongside war crimes and crimes against humanity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:108
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image8-47.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:110
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Stop Ecocide activists pose in front of a familiar pink boat. Photo: Stop Ecocide*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:112
msgid ""
"The [worst punishment](https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2019/mar/28/"
"destruction-earth-crime-polly-higgins-ecocide-george-monbiot/) currently "
"faced by people, businesses and states wreaking irreversible destruction on "
"habitats is a fine or an order to pay compensation. Ecocide’s absence from "
"international law represents a gaping hole - and one that could make the "
"difference between our extinction and survival."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:114
msgid ""
"If you want to help close this gap, the Stop Ecocide campaign has a [number "
"of ways](https://www.stopecocide.earth/get-involved-summary/) that you can "
"get involved."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "Israel Rebellion Brings Big Shit & Blockages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "**13 - 27 DEC | Ashkelon, Petah Tikva, Jerusalem.**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:120
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image10-47.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:122
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Rebels in Ashkelon find an alternative use for lengths of pipe. Photo: XR Israel*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:123
#, no-wrap
msgid "[XR Israel](https://xrisrael.earth/?fbclid%3DIwAR1e3St4IaFwP_euDniPewf5EgiBIhniXZv8aCvywEmU5ZVw_0elmtWj1xI/) launched a fortnight of nationwide actions last month, with the rebellion wave kicking off in the coastal city of Ashkelon.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "40 brave rebels [blocked the entrance](https://www.facebook.com/watch/live/?v%3D379233289844018%26ref%3Dwatch_permalink%26t%3D4789/) to both the giant coal-fired Rothberg Power Station and the [Eilat Ashkelon Pipeline Company](https://www.eapc.com/), whose pipeline pumps millions of barrels of crude oil every day between ports on the Mediterrean and Red Sea.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:127
#, no-wrap
msgid "Rebels managed to block traffic to the sites for two hours and recruit more rebels to their cause. An affinity group focused on the pipeline is now being set up.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:130
msgid ""
"A fissure in the pipeline in 2014 flooded the Evrona Nature Reserve with "
"oil, and was labelled one of Israel's worst [environmental catastrophes]"
"(https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/israeli-oil-spill-is-bad-news-for-a-"
"precious-nature-"
"preserve/2014/12/17/7855e726-7fd7-11e4-9f38-95a187e4c1f7_story.html/). "
"Nevertheless the pipeline’s operator recently secured a lucrative [oil deal "
"with the United Arab Emirates](https://www.spglobal.com/platts/en/market-"
"insights/latest-news/oil/102020-israeli-pipeline-company-to-transport-uae-"
"oil-via-red-sea-med-network/)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:132
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image14-47.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Rebels tend to a supersize turd in Migdal Group’s lobby. Signs read ‘Greenwash: Same Shit, Now in Green’ & ‘Diverting Attention, Not Investments’. Photo: XR Israel*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "A week later rebels in the central city of Petah Tikva entered the lobby of Migdal Group, one of the biggest pension funds in Israel. To encourage the group to stop greenwashing their dirty investments, the plucky rebels brought a big pile of fake excrement with them and [basted it with a generous supply of green slime](https://www.facebook.com/377148726388792/videos/879345809536370/).  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:137
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migdal invests over $1.5 billion a year in fossil fuels, and has a history of branding itself sustainable with little evidence. But following the rebel action the company stated it will apply [environmental and social criteria to investment choices](https://www.timesofisrael.com/israeli-investment-house-scores-first-with-pledge-not-to-invest-in-fossil-fuels/) and ditched recently bought stock in the oil company Delek.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:140
msgid ""
"The rebellion wave closed in the capital Jerusalem. 100 rebels disrupted the "
"city for several hours by [blocking the two exits](https://www.facebook.com/"
"XRisrael/videos/456717758820274/) of the Ministry of Energy, where the Prime "
"Minister recently raised Israel’s renewable energy target to 30%, even "
"though the current 17% target is far from being met, underlining how talking "
"targets can bear little relation to action on the ground."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "African World Heritage Site Plundered for Canadian Oil."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:144
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Ongoing | Botswana, Namibia**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:146
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image23-47.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:148
#, no-wrap
msgid "*The Okavango Delta.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:150
msgid ""
"The Kavango Basin is a vast water system that spreads across Namibia, "
"Botswana and the Okavango Delta, a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of the "
"planet’s largest wetlands."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:152
msgid ""
"Rather than protect this unique habitat, home to endangered species and the "
"world’s largest elephant population, last year both Namibia’s and Botswana’s "
"governments gave Canadian oil company ReconAfrica the rights to drill it. "
"The company has been given an area bordering 3 national parks upstream of "
"the Okavango Delta, and started drilling test boreholes in December."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:154
msgid ""
"Local activists from groups including [Frack Free Namibia](https://www."
"facebook.com/FrackFreeNamibiaAndBotswana/) and [Fridays For Future Windhoek]"
"(https://www.facebook.com/fffwhk/) have scrambled to mount a resistance "
"since learning of Recon’s plans. With the support of XR Africa and others, "
"they’ve launched an [online petition](https://www.rainforest-rescue.org/"
"petitions/1231/keep-the-oil-industry-out-of-africas-natural-treasures"
"%23more/) and [media campaign](https://www.presstv.com/"
"Detail/2020/12/17/640896/THE-OKAVANGO-OIL-FIELDS/) to raise awareness."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:156
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image13-47.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:158
#, no-wrap
msgid "*A Namibian activist with a clear message for ReconAfrica.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:160
msgid ""
"ReconAfrica is likely [to use fracking](https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/"
"article/2020-09-16-mystery-shrouds-plans-to-start-fracking-near-namibias-"
"kavango-river-and-botswanas-tsodilo-hills/) to plunder more oil, potentially "
"endangering the water supply of millions of people in a desert region. If "
"this wasn’t bad enough, one area marked for extraction is the home of the "
"Kalahari San, an indigeonous people already stressed by migration and the "
"changing climate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "This story is a stark example of neo-colonialism, with a Western company helping itself to a region’s resources at the expense of all life around it. Expect many more actions, and a growing international campaign, to stop the destruction.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:163
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Rebels of Oz: Brains Heart Courage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "**7 - 13 December | Australia**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:168
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image19-47.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:170
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Hot off the press - Murdoch lies. Photo: Julian Meehan*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:172
msgid ""
"A wave of coordinated actions rippled through Australia last month. The "
"ripples started in Melbourne’s Central Business District, where the emphasis "
"was on exposing [the planet killing lies of the Murdoch press](https://"
"twitter.com/xrebellionaus/status/1336562785665253377/8ZHsi). Rebels from XR "
"Victoria used tripods, banners and some good old fashioned theatrics to "
"block a major intersection."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:174
msgid ""
"A few days later the city hosted a blockade of Victoria’s Department of "
"Health. 4 rebels glued themselves to the entrance while a dozen more staged "
"a ‘die-in’ outside - symbolic victims of the climate and pandemic crises."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:176
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/image6-47.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:178
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Rebels rest in peace outside Victoria’s Department of Health. Photo: Julian Meehan*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2021-01-12-global-newsletter-47.md:180
